<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Class/Race Summary (Battle Tactics) Query</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?DarkBlight">DarkBlight</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:09 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Class/Race Summary (Battle Tactics) Query<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>There is little information (anywhere) regarding character setup.

<P>The current classes that seem to be favorable on the PvP server apparently are: Monks, Mages, and Rouges? Could someone be kind enough to illustrate the reasons for these preferences?
<P>Summary of Ogre Shadow Knight:
<P>Advantages: Highest HP, Greatest Str, Greatest Stamina, Greater Infravision.
<P>Disadvantages: Hated by nearly every race in Norrath save for Dark Elfs and Trolls, Size ( proves to create "interesting" situations in tight dungeon corridors ;p ) Low Wis, Low Int ( but still higher than a trolls )
<P>*Most other races/class combo's info can be readily gleaned through message boards and the like but anything concerning Ogres and Trolls are hard to come by. Anything regarding these elusive wretches would be highly appreciated.*
<P>Any thoughts or first hand accounts that could be added to the above would be greatly appreciated.
<P>- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
<P>Just as in Ultima favored tatics in the art of killing are starting to develop in Norrath.
<P>The ( slim ) below list briefly touches on skills/spells that are being extensively used in our bloody art. Feel free to add to this.
<P>Root ( Paralysis, which basically prevents prey from making a break to the zone or guards
<P>BackStab ( Double the amount of damage when striking at the back- Tried and true Rogue ability )
<P>Various offensive mage spells ( Once casted the poor sod at the receiving end can't do much to "dodge" or run away from the affects of direct damage spells )
<P>Are fighting styles strongly dependent on the class one is using? If so, which fighting styles do you prefer above the rest?
<P>Many Thanks
<P>DarkBlight
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
